# Vision Meta Images

When a detection action captures or processes screen regions during macro execution, save debug frames via `SaveMetaImage` or `SaveMetaImageLocked`. The helpers already gate on `PrefSaveMetaImages` — do not duplicate that check.

## Required saves by action

| Action | When | Purpose prefix |
|--------|------|----------------|
| Image Search | After capture | `searcharea` |
| Image Search | Per color mask | `cmask-{item}-{variant}` |
| Image Search | After matching | `founditems` (annotated) |
| OCR | After preprocessing | `ocr` |
| Semantic Search | After capture | `semantic-searcharea` |
| Semantic Search | After detection | `semantic-detections` (boxes + labels) |

## Conventions

- Call `SaveMetaImageLocked` inside an existing `WithOpenCV` block; otherwise use `SaveMetaImage`.
- Save the raw capture before inference; save an annotated clone after matching/detection.
- Purpose strings are sanitized (`sanitizeMetaPurpose`); use lowercase letters, digits, `-`, `_`.
- New detection actions must follow the same two-phase pattern (raw + annotated).

```go
// ✅ GOOD — semantic search meta saves
saveSemanticSearchAreaMeta(captureImg)
dets, err := detector.GetDetector().Detect(ctx, captureImg, opts)
// ...
saveSemanticDetectionsMeta(captureImg, dets)

// ❌ BAD — capture with no meta save when adding a new detection path
dets, err := detector.GetDetector().Detect(ctx, captureImg, opts)
```
